Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery closed vessel, possibly a neck-amphora; exterior: black-figure frieze to right, swan (top of head and wing missing; added red on wing, neck and breast) and, at right, possibly part of tail hanging and another undetermined creature; smudged dot rosette as filling ornament; below, triple dot band between pairs of lines; below, trace of lower frieze, possibly part of an animal ear.
Curator's comments: For parallels, see Cambridge Museum of Classical Archaeology NA205.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B102.18)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0010) (Phase 1)
